bib_record.title: Neutron Binding Energies from (d,p) Reactions and Nuclear Shell Structure

free_txt: The protons were detected by a triple
proportional counter and their range measured in
aluminum absorbers by the principle of "peaking," so
that only protons ending their range in the third
counter were counted. A parallel plate ionization
chamber was located at the entrance of the target
chamber in order to monitor the deuteron beam, and
this reduced the deuteron energy to about 14.0 MeV.
The relative cross sections are accurate
The targets used were about 20 mg/cm2 thick. The
deuteron beam was uniformly spread over 0.5 inch
